PART 3: GAP ANALYSIS — n=6 vs n=7
======================================================================
Gap pattern:
  n=6: max α₂ = 4, total pairs = 10, max/total = 4/10 = 2/5
       gap at α₂ = max-1 = 3
  n=7: max α₂ = 14, total pairs = 70, max/total = 14/70 = 1/5
       gap at α₂ = max-1 = 13

  Both have a gap at (max_α₂ - 1)!
  The max is achievable but max-1 is NOT.

  At n=6: 4 = C(4,2)/C(3,1) = 6/... hmm
  At n=6: max α₂ = 4 = C(4,2)-2 = 4
  At n=7: max α₂ = 14 = C(7,2) = 21... no, 14 = 2×7
  Regularity of uncovering:
  n=7: 14 both-cyclic pairs, each leaves 1 uncovered
       14 uncoverings / 7 vertices = 2 each (UNIFORM)
  n=6: 4 both-cyclic pairs, none leave uncovered (full partition)
       The max-α₂ configuration is SYMMETRIC in both cases

